-- Saudi Energy Consumption May Drop 60% With New Rules: Al-Riyadh
-- B y   D e e m a   A l m a s h a b i
-- 2013-05-06T10:08:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-06/saudi-energy-consumption-may-drop-60-with-new-rules-al-riyadh.html
Saudi Arabian energy consumption may
drop as much as 60% with implementation of new standards,  al-
Riyadh  reports, citing Saudi Electricity CEO Ali al-Barrak.
* Al-Barrak says govt. to introduce regulations for air
condition use and mandatory insulation requirements for
buildings: al-Riyadh
* Al-Barrak says 80% of domestic energy consumption is from air
conditioning: al-Riyadh
* Al-Barrak says raising electricity tariffs highly unlikely:
al-Riyadh  To contact the reporter on this story:
